This course explores how daily habits,
products, and lifestyles connect to global environmental and economic systems.
Students will examine sustainability issues through case studies from the EU,
Japan, and beyond. Each class poses a key question to encourage debate,
critical thinking, and reflection.

No prior knowledge of environmental studies or
the EU is required. The course emphasizes experiential

Students will develop critical and comparative
perspectives on how environmental challenges are shaped by history, culture,
and politics and how everyday choices connect to global change.

